674 A.2d 936 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND v. John Bradley KAISER. Misc. (Subtitle BV) No. 4,

Sept. Term, 1996.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. April 15, 1996.

ORDER

ELDRIDGE, Senior Judge.

Upon consideration of the Consent to Disbarment from the practice of law filed by John Bradley Kaiser, in accordance with Maryland Rule BV12d2, and the written recommendation of Bar Counsel, it is this 15th day of April, 1996

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that John Bradley Kaiser be, and he is hereby, disbarred by consent from the further practice of law in the State of Maryland; and it is further

ORDERED that the Clerk of this Court shall strike the name of John Bradley Kaiser from the register of attorneys, and pursuant to Maryland Rule BV13, shall certify that fact to the Trustees of the Clients’ Security Trust Fund and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State.
